In this press briefing, Press Secretary Robert Gibbs discusses the recent ruling on the health care law, stating that the administration disagrees with the ruling and believes that the law will be upheld. He also addresses concerns about the individual mandate and the tax deal, as well as the President's plans for the lame duck session. Gibbs mentions that the President will stay in Washington as long as Congress is in session and discusses the upcoming Afghan review. He also addresses questions about the President's relationship with Speaker Pelosi, the President's response to Bernie Sanders' filibuster, and the opposition to the DREAM Act by the American Legion. Gibbs does not comment on a statement by Ralph Nader or a memo from FOX News.